BlueField-3 SuperNIC Management Toolkit
Version: 1.0.0
Release Date: 2024-02-18

Components:
- bluefield-status.sh v1.0.0
- bluefield-rshim-check.sh v1.0.0
- bluefield-configure-ips.sh v1.0.0
- setup-spectrum-x-rhel.sh v1.0.0
- bluefield-quick-check.sh v1.0.0

Supported Hardware:
- NVIDIA BlueField-3 B3140H E-series SuperNICs
- Dell PowerEdge servers (tested)
- Other x86 servers with PCIe Gen4/Gen5 x16 slots

Supported Operating Systems:
- RHEL 8.x (tested on 8.9)
- RHEL 9.x (tested on 9.3)
- Rocky Linux 8.x
- Rocky Linux 9.x (tested on 9.3)
- Alma Linux 8.x
- Alma Linux 9.x

Tested Firmware:
- DOCA 3.2.1 LTS (bf-fwbundle-3.2.1-34_25.11-prod.bfb)

Requirements:
- Mellanox Software Tools (MST) or DOCA-Host package
- rshim package
- NetworkManager
- Root/sudo access

Change Log:

v1.0.0 (2024-02-18):
- Initial release
- Comprehensive status checking
- RShim management with auto-fix
- Spectrum-X RoCE acceleration configuration
- 8-rail network configuration with policy-based routing
- Complete documentation suite
- Troubleshooting guide
- Configuration examples

Known Issues:
- None at this time

Future Enhancements:
- Web-based monitoring dashboard
- Automated firmware update workflow
- Integration with configuration management tools (Ansible, Puppet)
- Support for Ubuntu/Debian distributions
- Performance monitoring and alerting
